00:24:02.679 --> 00:24:07.729
to a mood disorder and share that information
with other people, and come to more insights

00:24:07.729 --> 00:24:13.219
and better engagement, and so I want to leave
you with these three idea take aways. The

00:24:13.219 --> 00:24:16.899
first is that data means more when it's our
data. When we're given relevant information,

00:24:16.899 --> 00:24:22.700
it becomes incredibly more powerful driver
of behavior change. It's demonstrated not

00:24:22.700 --> 00:24:26.740
just in the studies that I talked about here
but in dozens of other studies, and the second

00:24:26.740 --> 00:24:30.519
is, that the more that we engage, the better
our health so this is the idea that I touched

00:24:30.519 --> 00:24:35.479
on, that when people are given a role in their
health and when they are participants of their

00:24:35.479 --> 00:24:39.239
health, they tend to have better outcomes.
Likewise, there was a study done, a meta analysis,

00:24:39.239 --> 00:24:43.700
of decision tools so these are specific tools
that when somebody say is diagnosed with a

00:24:43.700 --> 00:24:50.570
cancer and they want to know what chemotherapy
