There are statistics behind every one of these
decisions. This is what a decision tree is.

00:37:25.960 --> 00:37:33.809
My hope is that by making it clear that there
are always, that all of these choices have

00:37:33.809 --> 00:37:41.569
very clear numbers behind them and opportunities
to parse the numbers. Actively, proactively,

00:37:41.569 --> 00:37:46.191
that individuals can better go down these
courses and better understand what they are

00:37:46.191 --> 00:37:50.329
getting into. I think right now we, as you
say, look to our doctors to kind of guide

00:37:50.329 --> 00:37:57.309
us but the problem is that isn't the full
bevy of information that's out there. By necessity,

00:37:57.309 --> 00:38:01.799
they are a human filter, right? So we want
to be getting all the information but tailoring

00:38:01.799 --> 00:38:07.230
it to what our circumstances are so again,
that gets into the percentages of where do

00:38:07.230 --> 00:38:13.060
you fall, so to me that's an example of how
we need to be mindful of the fact that this

00:38:13.060 --> 00:38:14.760
is all probabilistic, that there are no sure
things.

00:38:14.760 --> 00:38:20.519
&gt;&gt; So as long as I'm up here, I'm going to
